  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Rohan, I'm Miss Maya. I love how passionate you are about football, it's such a big part of life in Kolkata. How was your day today?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hi Miss Maya, thanks! My day was a bit slow today. I watched a movie in Bengali, it was called \"Fats\" — you should watch it sometime. I also tried to practice some English, but I find it hard sometimes. Did you watch any good matches lately?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Nice to hear from you again. That movie sounds interesting, I'm glad you enjoyed it. Practicing English is a journey, and you're doing great! Did you watch any football matches recently?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yeah, I watch matches almost every day. Yesterday, I saw a Premier League game — Liverpool vs. Manchester United. Oh wow, what a match! It was 2-2, very exciting. I like Liverpool more, but United played well too. Sometimes I get confused with the rules, like offside. Do you follow English football?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Got it. Liverpool vs. Manchester United is always a big one, what part of the game was most exciting for you? I know the rules can get tricky, any one in particular that’s confusing?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The most exciting part was the first goal by Liverpool — it came in the 10th minute, and it was a amazing pass from the wing. But I get confused when a player is offside — I don’t get how the referee decides so fast. Also, I missed the second half of the match because I had to study for a bank exam. Tired now, honestly."
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Right, a quick wing pass sounds brilliant. I get that, the offside rule is tricky even for many fans. What part of the exam prep feels most tiring for you?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The most tiring part is solving a lot of numerical ability questions — it takes so much time and brain power. Also, I have to read a lot of banking awareness stuff, which is a bit boring. But I keep going, because I want to become a Bank PO. Do you know any good ways to improve English while studying for exams?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Got it. Numerical questions and banking reading sound heavy, what helps you stay focused when it gets tough? Mixing English practice into study breaks could work, like reading short news articles or summaries.\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Reading news articles sounds like a good idea — I’ll try that. Sometimes I get distracted while studying, so maybe switching to English news for a few minutes will help. Thank you, Miss Maya. I think I’ll go revise some math formulas now. Talk to you later!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Right, short breaks with English news could help. Talk to you later, good luck with the math formulas!\""
    }
  ],
  "memory_before": {
    "facts": {
